{"summary":"Accepted the targeted removals of legacy-only compatibility code and tests, and accepted the start-attempt matching fix. Rejected amendments that either remove a parameter that should instead be used, or over-harden optional linkage fields that are still legitimately unknown on some writes.","votes":[{"amendment_id":"fr-14-b5a477a3","decision":"accept","rationale":"`milestone_id` is always available on every write path in this store, while `read_task_runs_from_path` and `canonicalize_entry_for_write` currently hide missing data instead of failing fast. Making it a required `String` tightens the schema in the right place and removes unnecessary repair logic."},{"amendment_id":"fr-14-c5bceaec","decision":"accept","rationale":"The JSON renderer/parser is the canonical completion-details format in current code. Keeping comma-delimited legacy parsing and the replacement branch only preserves hypothetical old data, adds dead code, and can mask malformed new writes instead of surfacing them."},{"amendment_id":"fr-14-1ac821d9","decision":"accept","rationale":"The two named tests exist solely to preserve legacy deserialization/backfill behavior that should disappear with the corresponding code. Removing them is correct once that compatibility is removed; the `skipped_beads` test should only be dropped if that field is separately made required."},{"amendment_id":"fr-14-89e13c37","decision":"reject","rationale":"`_started_at` is unused today, but it is not merely dead API surface: it is the natural discriminator for attempt identity when `run_id` is absent or arrives later. Removing it would codify the current matching bug rather than fixing it."},{"amendment_id":"fr-14-c6ca5e53","decision":"reject","rationale":"The fail-fast direction is right for missing `milestone_id` and legacy journal repair, but this amendment is too broad as written. `run_id`, `plan_hash`, and `outcome_detail` are still legitimately optional when unknown at write time, so treating all optional/defaulted linkage fields as schema defects would overconstrain valid rows."},{"amendment_id":"fr-14-ec2442bd","decision":"accept","rationale":"Ignoring `started_at` makes start matching collapse distinct attempts and can strand phantom running rows when a replay later supplies `run_id`. Attempt matching needs to distinguish replay from a separate attempt, and `started_at` is the missing piece of that decision."}]}